# ============================================================
# COMPANY CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: company
scope: company.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for company.

## required_behavior
- company identity scope must be explicit
- ownership scope must be explicit
- actor allowance must be explicit
- activity allowance must be explicit
- disclosure allowance must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## policy_rules
Company policy constrains behavior by:
- company state
- ownership basis
- actor role
- declared activity scope
- policy boundary
- disclosure boundary

## actor_matrix
- owner
- executive
- operator
- reviewer
- regulator
- adapter

## disclosure_matrix
- public summary output
- masked operational output
- operator-scoped output
- reviewer-scoped output
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow bounded read for declared scope
- allow company action only for valid state and role
- allow review path for reviewer roles
- deny hidden ownership claims
- deny hidden authority widening
- deny out-of-scope company activity

## escalation_rules
When ownership,
authority,
state,
or activity meaning is unclear,
the company path must stop and escalate.

## failure_codes
- COMPANY_POLICY_IDENTITY_DENIED
- COMPANY_POLICY_STATE_DENIED
- COMPANY_POLICY_ACTIVITY_DENIED
- COMPANY_POLICY_BOUNDARY_DENIED
- COMPANY_POLICY_ESCALATION_REQUIRED

## review_checklist
- actor matrix exists
- disclosure matrix exists
- allowed/denied matrix exists
- escalation rules exist
